📘 in Operator — STRING NOTES

🔹 What is in?
in is a membership operator used to check whether a substring exists inside a string.

🔹 Output Type
 It always returns a Boolean:
  + True → substring is found
  + False → substring is not found

🔹 Syntax
substring in string

🔹 Uses in Data Analytics
Searching keywords
Cleaning text
Filtering data
Validating inputs
Checking patterns (emails, categories, names)

🔹 Examples
"Python" in "Python for Beginners"      # True
"java" in "Python for Beginners"       # False

🔹 Case-sensitive
"world" in "World"   # False